testCase.name: handleDropdown should return an array of options based on the status, isChecker, locked, and permissions parameters
handleDropdown should filter out "deactivate" and "activate" options if user does not have "CREATE_PRODUCT" permission
handleDropdown should filter out "modify" option if user does not have "CREATE_PRODUCT" permission and is not a checker
handleDropdown should return an array with only "view" option if locked parameter is true and "view" option exists
handleDropdown should return an empty array if locked parameter is true and "view" option does not exist
handleDropdown should return an array with only "view" option if isChecker parameter is true and "view" option exists
handleHeaders should filter out 'created_by' when isChecker is true
handleHeaders should filter out 'approved_By' when isChecker is false
handleDownload should generate CSV for requests category
handleDownload should generate CSV for product category
handleDownload should not generate CSV if downloadData is empty
initiateDownload should download all requests when category is "requests"
initiateDownload should not call download functions when category is not "all products" or "requests"
initiateDownload should call downloadProducts with the correct parameters when category is Investments
initiateDownload should call downloadRequests with the correct parameters when category is not Investments
initiateDownload should not call downloadProducts or downloadRequests when category is not defined or has an invalid value
getSearchResult should call setSearchResults with an empty array when value is empty
getSearchResult should call getRequests with the correct parameters when category is Requests
getSearchResult should call setSearchResults with an empty array when value is null
getSearchResult should not call setSearchResults when category is not a valid StatusCategoryType
